SIMPLE: unaffected
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unaffected
<hw>Un`af*fect"ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not
affected or moved; destitute of affection or emotion;
uninfluenced.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A poor, cold, unspirited, unmannered,⟦br⟧
Unhonest, <qex>unaffected</qex>, undone fool.</q> <rj><qau>J.
Fletcher.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Free from affectation; plain; simple; natural; real;
sincere; genuine; <as>as, <ex>unaffected</ex> sorrow</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Un`af*fect"ed*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Un`af*fect"ed*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unafiled</ent>⟦br⟧
